	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok im confused? the halfling has 85 stamina the same as a human, that is where get life so how do humans have more? they are 20 wooping points less in agi than both halflings and WE, with agi being arguably (and in my opinion is) the second most important attribute in a druid, are another wooping 15 pts less than halflings in dex as stated 5 pts less in wis, are the same as WE in charisma and int. the only thing they are higher in is str and thats only by 5 pts. <br><br>So in summary in order for humans to bring their sta,agi,dex, and wis just to even with a halfling,BASE stats they would need 40 pts, 10 pts more than they are given and to a wood elf 30 pts using all their pts just to break even wear as a halfling would only need to invest 5 pts in str to even out with a human in str and still be higher in most every important stat to a druid with 25 pts to max thier wis still.<br><br>This all creates a deficit in humans that will require much more use of items to even out what wood elves and halflings start out with after adding thier additional points the human had to use to break even with thier base stats.<br><br>Add to this humans get no race abilities, like hide and sneak, and that halflings on top of all this get the fastest exp gain. not to mention humans cant see at night.<br><br>Not to say ye shouldnt be proad of being a human druid, after all ye are a rare animal, just seemed ye were glossing over the true difference in the different races, the attributes can be easily seen on eqdruids.com all together to compare if ye want.<br>&nbsp;<br>Fiddo Lupineopolus<br>Cazic Thule<br>What do you mean being lazy is no way to live? It's the only thing I'm good at.</td></tr>
